

github


IssueCommentEvent -> comment-added

PullRequestEvent -> 'opened' -> PatchsetCreated
PullRequestReviewEvent  -> 'submitted' -> Comment Added (approved)

PushEvent

CreateEvent

DeleteEvent



Gerrit Events(in zuul layout.yaml):


*    Patchset Created
*    Change Restored
*    Comment Added
*    Ref Updated

Zuul also have a 'project-change-merged' to do mergability checks(merge check pipeline), but github handles this for us.


*    Assignee Changed
*    Change Abandoned
*    Change Merged
*    Draft Published
*    Dropped Output
*    Hashtags Changed
*    Project Created
*    Reviewer Added
*    Reviewer Deleted
*    Topic Changed

